Ident

Source: R/General_methods.R
Ident.Rd

Ident

Ident(struct, id)

# S4 method for RHermesExp,numeric
Ident(struct, id)

Arguments

struct

An RHermesExp object
id

The number corresponding to the inclusion list you want to access

Value

The identification data.frame with the RHermes_MS2Exp at position id.

See also

Other Getters: Cluster(), DB(), IL(), MS2Data(), PL(), SOI(), adlist()

Author

Roger Gine

Examples

struct <- readRDS(system.file("extdata", "exampleObject.rds",
                             package = "RHermes"))
Ident(struct, 1)
